## Simple Server Status
## http://github.com/joet3ch/simple-server-status

=Description=
A super lightweight service monitor.  Checks the connectivity to various services and displays results in web ui.

=Requirements=
tested with python 2.6
web.py [ http://webpy.org/ ] (test with v0.34)
MySQLdb
urllib2
/sbin/vpnc
/sbin/vpnc-disconnect

=Setup=
- Move 'webpy/' to './Classes/'
- Create database 'sss' using the 'schema.sql' file
- Add database details to 'config.py'
- Add cron job for 'launch_checks.py'
- Run app 'python launch_web.py' (add to your system's startup)

=Usage=
- Add/modify services in the database table 'sss.services'
- Navigate to http://<your_ip>:8080/ 

== Capabilities ==
- mysql
	- database existance
	- auth

- tcp
	- ip up
	- port listening
	- name resolution

- http
	- 
	
- ipsec
	- endpoint connectivity
	- auth
	- communications to host via tunnel